				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13481633#post-4720042</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13481633/scp-5116#post-4720042</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Wed, 15 Jul 2020 09:59:31 +0000</pubDate>
								<wikidot:authorUserId>6522165</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>While the concept itself is fun, I feel the article tries to cram multiple elements together at an unnatural pace. You have the consoles, the demonic entities, and a hole in Dan Dunn's basement. None of these are fleshed out, and they're all introduced at breakneck speed. There's some tonal issues as well. From what I can tell, the demonic entities are separate from SCP-5116-A, but I can't discern that from the text. In fact, I didn't even realize it until I was near the end of the article. It's tightly written, but it doesn't work with what's trying to be done. Delving a little more into the history and purpose behind the anomaly, even just a tiny bit, would've worked wonders for the piece.</p> <p>-1, unfortunately</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
